    <description>The Laboratory for Atmospheric and Space Physics (LASP) McPherson Vacuum UltraViolet Analytical Spectrophotometer (VUVAS) is a Seya-Namioka scanning-grating monochromator (McPherson, Inc. model 234/302, https://mcphersoninc.com/pdf/234302.pdf). It is designed for high-performance analysis in the ultraviolet spectrum, typically ranging from about 100 nm to 200 nm. It combines the capabilities of a monochromator (Model 234) and a detector system (Model 302) for precise measurement of light in the vacuum UV region.  </description>
